note: Title from introduction (f. 2v); other title from added note (f. 3r).

msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: 15th-century manuscript of 13th-century Arabic commentary on Euclid's Elements, with numerous diagrams in and marginal annotations around the text and additional commentary on leaves following the text.

persName.#text: Ṭūsī, Naṣīr al-Dīn Muḥammad ibn Muḥammad, 1201-1274
طوسي، نصير الدين محمد بن محمد،

supportDesc.extent: 213 leaves : 170 x 87 (114 x 48) mm. bound to 180 x 111 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, i (modern paper) + 213 + i (modern paper); [1-213] ; modern foliation in pencil, upper left recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed.

decoNote: Small geometric diagrams in red ink with black letters or black ink with red letters throughout.

binding.p: Modern Western red leather rebinding, blind-stamped with gilt-stamped spine; spine title "Tahrir al-Iqlidis, Euclidis elementa geometrica, 1458".

origin.p: Copy completed at the end of Rabīʻ al-Awwal A.H. 890 (April 1485).

provenance: Numerous ownership notes and seals, 15th century through 19th century.
Sold by Sam Fogg Ltd. (London), Dec. 1998, to Lawrence J. Schoenberg.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2011.
